This map origonaly started with the need for new maps in the clan Exiled gg/dm server. You can find the server at this IP: 69.90.119.135:27015

The map was drawn out by Killer, one of the leaders of the clan, and the drawn version of the map was given to me. I worked for about 2 days (total of about 23 hours) on this map. It took several compiles to get the lighting just perfect to work with the map how I needed it to. It's made so that it is a little dark, very bright in the buildings, and you can't see much of the sky. It's suppose to look like you're in a huge canyon sorta place. I thought I portrayed this canyon look fairly well. 

The map includes about 100 spawn points (although I wouldn't recomend using that many people for this map), by zones, several places to go, and well organized boxes in the inside of the buildings for strategy.

I made this map for the Exiled clan's server, but once it was done and everyone liked it, I decided I'd post it up on here. If you'd like to learn more about clan Exiled, visit our website at www.exiledclan-home.com. Or visit us in one of our many servers, you can get information about the servers at the website as well.

gg_egypt
by Jeremy "Air" Hurley



** Supports 40 players (20 spawns for each team)
** HE grenade on each roof
** Bombsite under the huge pyramid in the middle
** 5 pyramids total
** Great for low gravity too
** Lots of fun !!!


   This map was released on 5/27. I made this map in about 4 days off and on. I put around 30 hours of work into this map.

   Three of the five pyramids you can climb all over on. The other two you can actually go INSIDE and UP for a great sniping spot!

   This map was a lot of fun to make but at the same time very tedious. As usual, I began to obsess about finishing it and so I couldn't stop working on it.

   I didn't get to make the ground have displacements. I didn't really want it to, though. I also didn't add scenery to the 3d skybox but why bother? This map is already great and already a large enough file size.

  Playtests indicate the map is a blast. Framerates are very good, too. All in all it's an awesome map whether you are playing 1v1 or 20v20. This map also accomodates low-gravity very nicely!

ENJOY !!!


Jeremy "Air" Hurley
hurley@cox.net

|gg_edgecl by A.Werner aka Murf|
|------------------------------|

I dedicated a day to learn cell shading and tried it out on this map.
It's pretty cool but time consuming. I wish I could have done a larger map, but shading requires quite a big number of brushes.
You will notice the floating crates. I had to choose between floating crates or a bugged shade, because I don't really know how to make shades blend. If you have any ideas I'll be glad to launch a fix soon enough.

The textures of this map are the key colors of the game "Mirror's Edge", red and white, which is probably why the map is called "edgecl" ("cl" for cell).

The NAV file is included.

Thank you Karatekäfer for skybox and Lost for cell shading tut.

Hope you enjoy the map just as much as I enjoyed making it!

Don't forget to assess!

A.Werner

This map is specifically made for DZK (Deutscher Zocker Kreis) but may well be enjoying to play for other servers aswell. Like said it is a small tribute map for a gungame server of them.
It gets it's name from the topview, where you can read the letters "D Z K" in the form of a house and swimming pool. There's a little monitor in the house that shows the topview aswell (aswell as players who walk about outside).

Also this map is my first map that contains a custom radar, meaning you can pinpoint the positions of spotted enemies on the minimap (aswell as the overview when spectating). It is a little buggy at the CT-spawn, but it functions alright.
